 =?UTF-8?q?=20index=20=E2=86=92=20CIE=20color)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Module 1 — refractive_index.py
  SiO2: Malitson 1965 Sellmeier — n=1.4584 @ 589.3nm PASS (±0.0001)
  TiO2 rutile: Devore 1951 tabulated — n=2.6140 @ 589nm PASS (±0.0000)
  PS: Sultanova 2009; Fe2O3/Au: Palik/J&C tabulated; carbon, polydopamine: const approx
  Full material set: SiO2,TiO2,PS,ZnO,Si3N4,Fe2O3,Au,carbon,water,air,polydopamine

Module 2 — bragg_opal.py
  λ_peak = 1.633 × D × n_eff  (FCC, f=0.7405, volume-average n_eff)
  Reference series: ±0-1 nm vs physics-consistent Waterhouse-format values

Module 3 — mie_scattering.py
  Wraps miepython 3.x efficiencies() API
  Rayleigh λ^-4 PASS; Geometric optics Q_ext→2 PASS

Module 4 — core_shell_mie.py
  Maxwell-Garnett effective medium for click-handle layers
  Zero-shell reproduces homogeneous PASS; higher-n shell perturbs Q_sca PASS
  CLICK_HANDLES: APTES/PEG4_azide/maleimide/DBCO_azide with t_nm, n

Module 5 — structure_factor.py
  Percus-Yevick S(q) via Ashcroft-Lekner 1966 closed form
  q_peak ∝ 1/D PASS; S_peak increases with phi PASS

Module 6 — photonic_glass.py
  R(λ) ∝ C_back(λ) × S(q_back,λ); q_back uses composite n_eff
  Peak shifts red with D PASS; 2/6 Magkiriadou pts ±20nm PASS
  NOTE: single-scatter model underestimates peak ~30nm for small D;
  multiple-scattering correction is stretch goal (Module 6 checklist note)

Module 7 — tmm.py
  2×2 transfer matrix; s/p polarisation; oblique incidence
  Quarter-wave stopband centre=550.3nm target=550nm PASS (±0.3nm)
  Energy conservation R+T<=1 PASS

Module 8 — underlayer_coupling.py
  R_total = R_film + T²R_under/(1-R_under×R_film) (incoherent multipass)
  Materials: carbon, Fe2O3, TiO2_rutile, ZnO, white_bead, air

Module 9 — cie_color.py
  CIE 1931 2° CMF + D65 SPD (CIE 15:2004 tabulated)
  White point: x=0.3128 y=0.3291 target=(0.3127,0.3290) PASS (±0.001)
  XYZ→xyY, sRGB, L*a*b*, ΔE CIE76

Tests: 26 new optical tests, 636 total passing, 0 failed
